news.title: RHB set to introduce two residential schemes for middle-income groups in Jaipur
news.para: The housing schemes in Mansarovar are meant for two middle-income groups. The two schemes – named Ganga and Gulmohar – will have 160 flats of 2-BHK and 3-BHK categories.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body extends rebate scheme for property tax payment till May 30
news.para: Between April 8 and 28, the AMC received advance property tax from over 3.95 lakh residents, with a collection of Rs 482.89 crore. The total rebate amounted to Rs 52.78 crore.

news.title: Lucknow: LDA forms committee to address Basant Kunj’s issues
news.para: Officials said that launched in the 1990s, the Basant Kunj scheme covered 1,353 acres spread across ten sectors (A to J), involving land of around 800 farmers and inhabitants

news.title: SC orders CBI probe into Supertech projects in NCR
news.para: The apex court previously said thousands of homebuyers were affected by the subvention scheme, where banks paid 60 to 70 per cent of the home loan amount to the builders without projects being completed within the stipulated time.

news.title: Developers pivot to offer GCCs more than just offices
news.para: Setting up a GCC in India involves creation of an ecosystem comprising physical infrastructure, people and business operations, said Arjun Aggarwal, managing director at Bhartiya Urban.

news.title: Gensol pulled out of DLF office deal a month before Sebi order
news.para: Gensol had signed letter of intent (LoI) in 2024 but conveyed to the developer a month ago that it cannot sign the final agreement.

news.title: Lucknow civic body urges citizens to pay property tax by April 30 for 10% rebate
news.para: Officials said that from May 1, the rebate will be reduced to 8% for online payments and 6% for offline payments. Citizens are encouraged to pay online to avoid crowds.

news.title: Bombay HC strikes down GST demand on TDR used by real estate developer
news.para: Senior counsel Akshay Naik, assisted by Abhishek Bhoot, argued that the project did not involve any transfer or purchase of development rights or floor space index (FSI) from external sources.

news.title: Odisha RERA faces closure as two members set to retire in May
news.para: According to the Odisha Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016, the govt is required to initiate recruitment processes before such positions become vacant.

news.title: Builders causing delays in Mumbai's redevelopment will face consequences: Piyush Goyal
news.para: He acknowledged the timely and quality completion of this specific project by the developer but made it clear that the government will not tolerate negligence, corruption, or delays in SRA redevelopment.

news.title: Mumbai: Mhada opens 114 layouts for redevelopment
news.para: Mhada is one of the biggest landlords in Mumbai, owning approximately 2,000 hectares. Its smallest layout is spread over 10 acres while the largest is spread over 140 acres.

news.title: Stakeholders raise concerns over lack of clarity in Uttarakhand RERA regulations
news.para: RERA officials have also clarified that for five years from the date of possession, all structural and quality-related maintenance issues are promoter's responsibility.

news.title: HC quashes Haryana governmmet's order to grant RERA recovery powers
news.para: Granting recovery powers to Rera officers, the court said, was a "violation of the legal framework" set under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act (RERA), 2016.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA introduces new guidelines to prioritise hearing of complaints
news.para: The move, formalised via a circular issued earlier this month and implemented with immediate effect, aims to provide expedited relief to complainants facing extraordinary situations.

news.title: Patna: Slow progress in linking land records to Aadhar despite May 31 deadline
news.para: According to sources in the revenue and land reforms dept, only 17.45 lakh people have so far applied for Aadhaar seedings and around 13 lakh applications have already been processed in the district.

news.title: Hero Realty to invest Rs 3,000 crore in residential project in Gurugram
news.para: The company, backed by Sunil Kant Munjal's Hero Enterprise, had formed a joint venture with Gurugram-based Saheb Enterprise to develop a premium residential complex in Sector 104, Gurugram.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to transform 57 municipalities into smart cities with Rs 40,000 crore investment
news.para: The department has already developed 17 smart cities in line with this vision. The government allocated a budget of ₹40,000 crore for this project, with ₹145 crore already sanctioned as initial funding.

news.title: Embassy Office Parks REIT raises Rs 675 crore short-term debt to repay loans
news.para: The yield is 7.075 per cent and these commercial papers are proposed to be listed on the Wholesale Debt Market Segment of BSE Ltd.

news.title: PNB Housing's net profit rises 25.30% in Q4 FY25
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at ₹2,036.78 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 12.28 per cent from ₹1,813.97 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra government to acquire 8,000 acres land in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar: CM
news.para: Industries too are positive about coming here," the CM said. Speaking about infrastructure development in the city, he said a ring road will be constructed to connect industrial zones.
